1. 나는 아이를 부모로 만들었습 # Hiroshi Miyamoto  Hiroshi Miyamoto (jap. 宮本 博 Miyamoto Hiroshi; ur. 1952) – japoński językoznawca, specjalizujący się w języku japonii i indoeuropejskim.  Hiroshi Miyamoto宮本 博  Hiroshi Miyamoto urodził się w 1952 roku w prefekturze 北海道 札幌. W 1975 roku ukończył Uniwersytet Tokijski, zdobywając stopień licencjacki z językoznawstwa japońskiego. W 1980 roku uzyskał doktorat z językoznawstwa na Uniwersytecie Princeton, gdzie pod kierunkiem Johna Whitneya Kennedy'ego i Bernarda Comptona Pierce'a opublikował swoją rozprawę doktorską poświęconą procesom fonetycznym w języku japonii.  Po ukończeniu studiów Miyamoto pracował jako asystent profesorski w Uniwersytecie Pensylwanii oraz Uniwersytecie Yale’a. Od 1985 roku jest pracownikiem Uniwersytetu Chicago, gdzie objął stanowisko profesora japoniologii i językoznawstwa. Miyamoto jest autorem licznych publikacji naukowych z dziedziny językoznawstwa, w tym monografii The Sound Laws of Japanese (1984) i The Sounds of the World's Languages (1999), a także współredaktorem Enciklopedii japońskiej (2002) i The Handbook of Japanese Syntax (2003).  Miyamoto jest znany z swojej pracy nad porównywaniem języka japońskiego z indoeuropejskimi językami, w szczególności z angielskim i francuskim. Badając procesy fonetyczne i morfologiczne w tych językach, Miyamoto doszedł do wniosku, że ich wspólny przodkiem jest język, którym byłby prawdopodobnie język kaukaski.  Hiroshi Miyamoto jest członkiem wielu naukowych organizacji i komitetów, w tym Japonskiego Towarzystwa Językoznawczego, Amerykańskiego Towarzystwa Językoznawczego i Międzynarodowego Towarzystwa Językoznawstwa. W 2002 roku otrzymał Nagrodę im. Kiyoshi Shimizu za całokształt osiągnięć w językoznawstwie.

1. 으시대다'이 바른 말이며, 이는 올바른 구문입니다. 으시대다'는 영어 문법에서 순차적 형태인 두 개의 같은 단어의 초점이 반대 방향으로 배치되어 형태의 순서가 반대임을 나타냅니다. 예를 들어, "이 책은 그녀에게 그녀에게 이 책을 주었습니다."라고 말하면 "이 책은 그녀에게 이 책을 주었습니다."라는 뜻이 됩니다. 이 예에서 "그녀에게"는 으시대 구문의 초점이 반대 방향으로 배치되어 순차적 형태로 반영됩니다. 이러한 접근 방식을 이렇게 하기 때문에 '그렇게 으시대다가 낭패 볼라'가 바람직한 문장이 됩니다.2. 이 문장은 올바르지 않습니다. '그렇게 으시대다가 낭패 볼라'는 순차적 형태의 으시대 구문으로 반드시 구성되어야 하지만 이 문장은 이를 위반합니다. "그렇게 으시대다가 낭패 볼라"라는 문장은 으시대 구문에 대한 형식적 규칙을 위반하는 두 개의 다른 단어, 즉 "그렇게"와 "그녀"를 사용하여 구성되어 있습니다. 으시대 구문은 두 개 이상의 단어를 사용하여 순차적 형태의 형태를 생성해야 합니다.

import com.amazonaws.services.dynamodbv2.AmazonDynamoDBClientBuilder; import com.amazonaws.services.dynamodbv2.document.DynamoDB; import com.amazonaws.services.dynamodbv2.document.Item; import com.amazonaws.services.dynamodbv2.document.Table; import com.example.s3.controller.AbstractS3Controller; import com.example.s3.dto.S3Object; import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired; import org.springframework.stereotype.Controller; import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping; import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestParam; import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.ResponseBody;  import java.util.HashMap; import java.util.Map;  @Controller public class DynamoDBController extends AbstractS3Controller {      private static final String TABLE_NAME = "items";      private String accessKey;     private String secretKey;      @Autowired     public DynamoDBController(String accessKey, String secretKey) {         this.accessKey = accessKey;         this.secretKey = secretKey;     }      @GetMapping("/dynamodb/items/{id}")     public ResponseEntity<S3Object> getItem(@PathVariable("id") String id) {         DynamoDB dynamoDB = getDynamoDB();         Table table = dynamoDB.getTable(TABLE_NAME);         Map<String, Object> key = new HashMap<String, Object>();         key.put("id", id);         Item item = table.getItem(key);         String contentType = item.get("contentType").toString();         String contentHash = item.get("contentHash").toString();         String etag = item.get("etag").toString();         String size = String.valueOf(item.get("size").longValue());         S3Object s3Object = new S3Object().withContentType(contentType)                 .withContentHash(contentHash)                 .withEtag(etag)                 .withSize(size);         return ResponseEntity.ok(s3Object);     }      @GetMapping("/dynamodb/items")     @ResponseBody     public Map<String, Map<String, String>> getAllItems() {         DynamoDB dynamoDB = getDynamoDB();         Table table = dynamoDB.getTable(TABLE_NAME);         Map<String, Map<String, String>> items = new HashMap<String, Map<String, String>>();         Items itemsItems = table.query();         for (Items itemsItemsItems : itemsItems) {             Map<String, String> item = new HashMap<String, String>();             item.put("id", itemsItemsItems.get("id").toString());             item.put("contentType", itemsItemsItems.get("contentType").toString());             item.put("contentHash", itemsItemsItems.get("contentHash").toString());             item.put("etag", itemsItemsItems.get("etag").toString());             item.put("size", String.valueOf(itemsItemsItems.get("size").longValue()));             items.put(itemsItemsItems.get("id").toString(), item);         }         return items;     }      private DynamoDB getDynamoDB() {         BasicAWSCredentials awsCredentials = new BasicAWSCredentials(accessKey, secretKey);         AmazonDynamoDB dynamoDBClient = AmazonDynamoDBClientBuilder.defaultClient();         return dynamoDBClient.getDynamoDB();     } }

 ```python
 future.utils.promises에서 import sleep
 
 def is_tuesday_tomorrow():
     return (futures.calendar.day_name(futures.calendar.day_of_week(datetime.now() + timedelta(days=1))) == "Tuesday")
 
 def ask_question():
     while True:
         question = input("내일 간식은 ")
         if question == "떡볶이":
             break
         print("잘못된 질문입니다. 떡볶이라고 입력하세요.")
         question = input()
         
         response = None
         if is_tuesday_tomorrow():
             response = f"떡볶이입니다!"
         else:
             response = f"떡볶기입니다!"
         
         print(response)
         
         input("입력을 입력하세요: ")
         
         answer = input()
         
         if answer == "yes":
             return response
         
         sleep(1)
 
 __name__ == "__main__":
     ask_question()

extends ASTNode> visitor) {     ASTNode curr = node.getLastChild();     while (curr != null) {       visitor.visit(curr);       node = (ASTNode)curr.getParent();       curr = node.getLastChild();     }   }    public static void rewrite(ASTNode node, @NotNull JavaLightTreeTraverser<?> traverser) {     traverser.traverse(node);   }    public static void rewrite(ASTNode node, @NotNull PsiRecursiveElementWalkingVisitor visitor) {     visitor.visitUnknownElements(node);     ASTNode curr = node.getLastChild();     while (curr != null) {       visitor.visitElement(curr);       node = (ASTNode)curr.getParent();       curr = node.getLastChild();     }   }    public static ASTNode replaceExpressionWithVariable(ASTNode expr, String variableName) throws IncorrectOperationException {     ASTNode assignedNode = new ASTNode(expr.getTreeParent(), expr.getTreeOffset());     ASTNode exprNode = TreeUtil.copyElement(expr);     ASTNode varNode = new ASTNode(expr.getTreeParent(), assignedNode);     varNode.addChild(variableName, ASTNode.LPAREN);     varNode.addChild(exprNode, ASTNode.RPAREN);     TreeUtil.delete(expr);     return varNode;   } }

1  온종일 비가 오다가 이제 왼종일이 되었습 package com.blamejared.compat.json.codec.zst;  import com.blamejared.compat.json.codec.zst.ZstEncoder.BitStream; import com.blamejared.compat.util.Range;  import java.io.IOException; import java.util.Arrays;  public class HuffmanTree {     private final int[][] dp;     private int[] freq;      public HuffmanTree(int[][] freq) {         this.freq = freq.length > 0 ? freq[0] : new int[0];         this.dp = new int[256][freq.length];          for (int i = 0; i < 256; i++) {             dp[i][0] = i;         }          for (int i = 0; i < freq.length; i++) {             int j = freq[i];             for (int k = 0; k < 256; k++) {                 int x = 255;                 int y = 0;                 while (x > 0 && k > j) {                     if (dp[k][x] != 255) {                         x--;                     } else {                         j = Math.min(j, k - dp[k][x]);                     }                     y++;                 }                 dp[k][j] = i + y;             }         }     }      public int decodeSymbol(int symbol, BitStream.Marker marker) throws IOException {         int len = 1;         int code = 0;         while (true) {             int[] path = new int[len];             path[0] = symbol;             int numNodes = 0;             for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {                 int curr = dp[symbol & (1 << len - i - 1)][code & (1 << len - i - 1)];                 path[i] = curr;                 numNodes += freq[curr];                 code <<= 1;             }             if (numNodes == 0) {                 break;             }             len++;         }         code >>>= 1;         return (code < 10) ? (path[0] >> code) : (path[0] >> code) + 256;     }      public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {         int[][] freq = { { 128, 9 }, { 64, 14 }, { 32, 1 }, { 16, 15 }, { 8, 13 }, { 4, 12 }, { 2, 11 }, { 1, 10 }, { 1, 9 }, { 1, 8 }, { 1, 7 }, { 1, 6 }, { 1, 5 }, { 1, 4 }, { 1, 3 }, { 1, 2 }, { 1, 1 }};         BitStream.Encoder encoder = new ZstEncoder(new HuffmanTree(freq));         BitStream.Marker marker = BitStream.Marker.Prepare(1024);         BitStream bs = new BitStream(marker, encoder);          int len = bs.writeSymbol(0, 10);         System.out.println("결과 바이트 길이: " + len);          BitStream.Marker marker2 = BitStream.Marker.Prepare(8);         bs = new BitStream(marker2, encoder);         len = bs.writeSymbol(0, 8);         System.out.println("결과 바이트 길이: " + len);     } }

Seaton, Alexander (Scotland; 1515–1542) historian, born in Scotland, in 1515, was a native of the county of Fifeshire. He was educated at St. Andrews, where he made great proficiency in literature, and became a celebrated scholar. Afterwards he became a member of the Scottish privy council, and was employed in several important embassies to foreign courts. He was also appointed one of the commissioners for visiting and reforming the abbeys in Scotland, and employed in other public duties of great trust and importance.  In 1541, he published his "History of the Affairs of Scotland," from the period of the invasion of that country by the English, in the reign of David I. to the death of James V. in 1542. This work, which is still highly valued, is written in a clear and elegant style, and contains much valuable information on the history of Scotland. Seaton's reputation as a scholar and a statesman was very great in his own country, and his loss was deeply regretted by all who knew him. He died in 1542.  Seaton was a man of great learning, and of an amiable and honorable character.
